        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 3:59AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 359 AM CDT/259 AM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Walker to near Trail
City to 6 miles east of Bush's Landing. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mobridge, Gettysburg, Mclaughlin, Onida, Selby, Herreid, Hoven,
Little Eagle, Bullhead, Wakpala, Pollock, Kenel, Java, Swiftbird,
Glenham, Agar, Mound City, Lebanon, Akaska, and Tolstoy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT/600 AM
MDT/ for central and north central South Dakota.</instruction>
